snippet.textDisplay:
I'm not a consumer of Bollywood content, but I'm always amazed when I see your react videos because it exposes me to a genre and filmic style that I'm not used to.
As far as CG goes, it seems that Bollywood is somewhere between early 2000s and current day Hollywood, so it'll be interesting to see where it goes in the next few years.
I've also noticed that, much like how many kung fu movies have floating magical acrobatics, the Bollywood action films have their own way of suspending the real-world physics. I wonder if this is something that will remain in the long term or whether it's part of the newness of technology available.
Great video and stay safe <3
